title: PPPP’s Khurram Karim Soomro wins PS-67 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan People’s Party Parliamentarians’ (PPPP) Khurram Karim Soomro has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-67, Tando Muhammad Khan-II, by securing 51,886 votes.
According to unofficial result issued by Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Qadir Bakhsh Magsi, Khadim-e-Sindh, who bagged vote 16,602.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 47.61 %.
